subSubSection.paragraph:
Morphological description
: Size 150–200 × 50–65 µm 
in vivo
, and 115–200 × 72–105 µm after protargol staining, body basically ellipsoid in shape with posterior end narrowed, both ends broadly rounded, left margin of anterior region ear-shaped, protruding to the left side and widest at 2/5 anterior portion (
Figs. 1A, B
; 
2A, B
). Dorsal side evidently vaulted in center and cell is flattened 3:2 dorsoventrally (
Fig. 2C
). Buccal field narrow, about 2/5 of body length.

