subSubSection.paragraph:
Infraciliature as shown in 
Figs. 1E, F
; 
2K
. Adoral zone of membranes (
AZM
) curves along anterior cell margin and bends conspicuously posteriad along right margin; and proximal end of 
AZM
extends somewhat obliquely towards buccal cavity (
Figs. 1E
; 
2L
). Bases of membranelles ca. 10 µm in length. Paroral (
PM
) (
Figs. 1E
; 
2L
, arrow) and endoral membrane (EM) (
Figs. 1E
; 
2L
, arrowhead) arched and optically intersected each other in posterior portion.

18–29 cirri in frontal area which form the non-typical bicorona, of which ca. 11 right ones arranged in a arc along anterior right margin, ca. 14 left ones arranged in an oblique line (
Figs. 1E
; 
2L
). Two bicorona rows terminated anteriorly near 
AZM
and not separated posteriorly from the midventral complex although in some specimens an inconspicuous gap was observed in the level of distal end of 
AZM
(
Fig 1E
, arrow). Two frontoterminal cirri (
FTC
) located between distal end of adoral zone and anterior end of right marginal row (
Figs. 1E
; 
2M
, arrowheads); mostly 4 buccal cirri (BC) lay close to paroral membrane (
Figs. 1E
; 
2M
, arrows). Midventral complex comprising of 21–32 midventral pairs, terminating just above the transverse cirri, the cirri of the pair conspicuously separated from each other (
Figs. 1E
). 8–13 transverse cirri (
TC
) densely arranged in a J-shaped row near posterior margin of cell (
Figs. 1E
; 
2O
, arrows). Cirri in marginal rows narrowly spaced; left marginal row (
LMR
) commencing at the cytostome level. Marginal rows almost confluent posteriorly (
Fig. 1E
). Bases of cirri associated with well impregnated fibers (
Fig. 2K
). Dorsal cilia about 4 µm long, consistently arranged in 3 complete rows, which extend whole length of body, each comprising about 30 pairs of basal bodies (
Fig. 1F
).
